1
00:00:44,362 --> 00:00:49,137
=The Hidden Heir Ye Chen=
(Adapted from "The Peerless Son-in-Law")

2
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:52,212
=Episode 29=

3
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:22,799
Dad,

4
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,159
everyone's here.

5
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:28,975
(Wu Donghai, head of the Wu family)

6
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,239
I thought Ye Chen

7
00:01:31,239 --> 00:01:32,879
was some kind of tough guy.

8
00:01:33,319 --> 00:01:34,680
Once my Twin Devils made a move,

9
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,439
he still ended up flat on the ground.

10
00:01:37,040 --> 00:01:38,400
You've already got what you wanted.

11
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,719
Can you leave now?

12
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:42,799
Watch your tone.

13
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,879
Show some respect.

14
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,439
Dad,

15
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:47,760
we're guests here.

16
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,940
Let's be a little more polite.

17
00:01:58,599 --> 00:01:59,280
Ms. Song.

18
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,640
Not happy to see us?

19
00:02:03,687 --> 00:02:06,009
Don't you always pride yourself
on being a gentleman?

20
00:02:06,050 --> 00:02:08,079
Never forcing people
to do things they don't want?

21
00:02:14,450 --> 00:02:16,120
That depends on my mood.

22
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,879
When I'm in a good mood,

23
00:02:18,879 --> 00:02:20,199
I like playing games the most.

24
00:02:23,039 --> 00:02:23,719
Wanting,

25
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:27,159
the game is about
to reach the best part.

26
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,520
If you chase us away now,

27
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,330
I'll be very unhappy.

28
00:02:35,125 --> 00:02:36,479
Mr. Wu, please make yourself

29
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:37,960
at home.

30
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,400
Go.

31
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,159
Take good care of Ms. Song.

32
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,000
Don't let anyone disturb her rest.

33
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:47,840
Understood.

34
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:50,237
(Chest pain. Trauma.)

35
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:52,100
(Emergency Room)

36
00:02:56,879 --> 00:02:58,520
The patient
is temporarily out of danger,

37
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,862
but his injuries are too severe.

38
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,120
He's still unconscious.

39
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,639
And his nerves were damaged too.

40
00:03:02,987 --> 00:03:04,625
There's a risk
he could end up paralyzed.

41
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:18,560
No matter how long it takes
for you to wake up,

42
00:03:21,759 --> 00:03:23,599
or what you become,

43
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,639
I'll stay with you.

44
00:03:37,879 --> 00:03:38,680
It's them.

45
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,310
What's wrong?

46
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,919
No, nothing.

47
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,680
Let him

48
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:50,879
rest and recover properly.

49
00:03:51,062 --> 00:03:52,987
(Emergency Room)

50
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:56,879
Mr. Hong.

51
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:57,520
Ms. Xiao.

52
00:03:58,010 --> 00:04:00,120
Is there something strange
about Ye Chen's injuries?

53
00:04:00,319 --> 00:04:00,919
No.

54
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,479
Everything's fine.

55
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:03,759
At a time like this,

56
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:05,120
what else can't you tell me?

57
00:04:09,439 --> 00:04:11,599
Ms. Xiao, this isn't a good place to talk.

58
00:04:12,199 --> 00:04:13,479
Can we go somewhere else?

59
00:04:14,719 --> 00:04:15,240
Alright.

60
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,879
You brat, you scared the life out of me.

61
00:04:28,975 --> 00:04:30,959
Old man, you scared me first.

62
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:33,040
You were the one who started it.

63
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,837
You started it first.

64
00:04:35,187 --> 00:04:37,549
You suddenly opened your eyes.

65
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:38,759
You could've at least groaned,

66
00:04:38,759 --> 00:04:39,800
or moved a finger.

67
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:41,439
But you suddenly opened your eyes.

68
00:04:41,439 --> 00:04:41,800
Alright.

69
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,040
My fault.

70
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:46,279
How are you feeling?

71
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,560
I'm perfectly fine.

72
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,505
Still strong as ever.

73
00:04:56,439 --> 00:04:57,480
You brat,

74
00:04:58,079 --> 00:05:00,720
you should
pay more attention to yourself.

75
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,319
I'm young and strong.

76
00:05:02,987 --> 00:05:04,575
Unlike you, you old...

77
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,759
Hit a sore spot, did you?

78
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:09,720
Muscles

79
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,920
throwing a little party now?

80
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:12,920
Serves you right.

81
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:16,199
You brat,

82
00:05:16,199 --> 00:05:17,480
you're lucky to still be alive.

83
00:05:17,639 --> 00:05:18,000
Here.

84
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,600
- That hurts.
- See?

85
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,160
Muscles throwing a little party now?

86
00:05:26,439 --> 00:05:27,399
Serves you right.

87
00:05:28,519 --> 00:05:29,279
Come on.

88
00:05:29,279 --> 00:05:30,439
Sit down.

89
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:31,959
Slowly.

90
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,439
Mr. Ye,

91
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:44,279
this whole incident was my fault
for not thinking it through.

92
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,519
I shouldn't have let you go alone.

93
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:49,839
Look at me now.

94
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:51,200
And you're only saying this now.

95
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,959
Isn't that a little too late?

96
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,560
Focus on recovering.

97
00:05:56,737 --> 00:05:57,800
Once you're healed,

98
00:05:58,045 --> 00:05:59,925
you have to play all the game toys

99
00:05:59,925 --> 00:06:01,084
you bought for me with me.

100
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,062
You owe me that.

101
00:06:03,462 --> 00:06:04,160
No backing out.

102
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,279
Looking at Senior Uncle's injury,

103
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,800
I could tell it was caused

104
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,519
by our sect's unique technique.

105
00:06:32,325 --> 00:06:33,205
In the world today,

106
00:06:33,205 --> 00:06:34,085
this technique is used

107
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:35,399
only by me,

108
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,560
my Senior Uncle,

109
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,319
and his two followers,

110
00:06:39,390 --> 00:06:40,439
Twin Devils of Zhen'nan.

111
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,480
Twin Devils of Zhen'nan?

112
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,040
The man is Yin Biao.

113
00:06:44,439 --> 00:06:45,439
The woman is Yin Lu.

114
00:06:45,839 --> 00:06:46,800
They're siblings.

115
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,160
Their father,

116
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,920
my master who taught me everything,

117
00:06:50,662 --> 00:06:51,535
was Yin Tianchou.

118
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,937
Duan Shuiliu killed my master.

119
00:06:54,462 --> 00:06:55,501
Yet those two

120
00:06:55,501 --> 00:06:56,837
not only took him as their master,

121
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:59,800
they also trained hard
and became very skilled.

122
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,759
if we followed him,

123
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,240
we could only live
in poverty and hardship.

124
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,120
Luckily that old man died early,

125
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:08,920
so it didn't stop us
from enjoying life with our master.

126
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:11,000
Worthless trash!

127
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:20,959
I know.

128
00:07:22,279 --> 00:07:23,720
I have no strength left for revenge.

129
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,720
Feeling disheartened,

130
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,879
I came to Jinzhou.

131
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:29,240
Later,

132
00:07:29,879 --> 00:07:31,000
they vanished

133
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,920
when the police came after them.

134
00:07:33,330 --> 00:07:35,399
I thought they had already
been brought to justice.

135
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:39,120
I didn't expect them to show up again.

136
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,937
These Twin Devils of Zhen'nan

137
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:42,287
are ruthless and cruel.

138
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,040
They're capable of anything.

139
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,800
They won't let this go easily.

140
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:46,879
We...

141
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,600
need to prepare early.

142
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:49,519
Yeah.

143
00:07:50,839 --> 00:07:52,199
Sihai, tell me,

144
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,759
what happened to Song Wanting?

145
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,000
She's been under the Wu family's control.

146
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,962
But she's safe for now.

147
00:07:59,137 --> 00:08:00,438
The former overlord of Jinzhou

148
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:02,519
is now controlled by this Wu guy

149
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,879
without any power to fight back.

150
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,800
They came with bad intentions.

151
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:07,560
That's right.

152
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,480
The Wu family's base is in Dongwu.

153
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:12,270
Their strength
has always surpassed the Song family.

154
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,399
The head of the Wu family is Wu Donghai,

155
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:16,199
the richest man in Dongwu,

156
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:18,000
working in real estate.

157
00:08:18,639 --> 00:08:20,000
According to Dongxue's report,

158
00:08:20,279 --> 00:08:21,800
after he entered the Song residence,

159
00:08:22,462 --> 00:08:23,581
he never came out again.

160
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:25,590
He even replaced all
of the Song family's

161
00:08:25,887 --> 00:08:26,720
bodyguards.

162
00:08:28,279 --> 00:08:28,879
This man

163
00:08:29,412 --> 00:08:30,399
is Wu Donghai.

164
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,079
He had no dealings

165
00:08:32,319 --> 00:08:33,199
with your parents.

166
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:34,839
After years of investigation,

167
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,720
I never really suspected him.

168
00:08:37,199 --> 00:08:37,720
But

169
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,039
it's still unclear

170
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:41,279
whether he was involved
in the car accident back then.

171
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:56,200
I remember now.

172
00:08:58,262 --> 00:09:00,092
He appeared
at the accident scene that year.

173
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,240
My dad must have sensed the danger.

174
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,720
So he sent the prescription formulas
away separately

175
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,110
instead of carrying them with him.

176
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,879
Even though Wu Donghai
caused that accident,

177
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,750
he didn't get the prescriptions.

178
00:09:15,679 --> 00:09:16,879
Your judgment is correct.

179
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:18,960
All these years,

180
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,279
I've been investigating.

181
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:23,399
He was afraid of being exposed,

182
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:26,200
so he stayed quiet all this time.

183
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:29,200
He had been watching from the shadows,
waiting for me to appear.

184
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,240
He only made his move

185
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:33,039
after I had all three prescriptions.

186
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:39,639
Unfortunately,

187
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:43,080
the prescriptions
still ended up in his hands.

188
00:10:05,687 --> 00:10:09,212
(Loading)

189
00:10:09,587 --> 00:10:10,879
(Please enter password)
What the heck is this?

190
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,799
Why does it need a password?

191
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,480
Don't worry, Mr. Ye.

192
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,039
Even if Wu Donghai

193
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:19,519
gets those three USB drives,

194
00:10:19,590 --> 00:10:21,120
he still can't unlock the prescription.

195
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:23,759
Your dad left a final safeguard.

196
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,360
What safeguard?

197
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:27,440
That prescription

198
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:28,879
was developed by your parents

199
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,325
to cure your illness.

200
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:33,080
The final password

201
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,200
is the mutation data

202
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:36,759
from your brain's neural genes.

203
00:10:38,159 --> 00:10:39,000
Me?

204
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,120
How dare they mess with me?

205
00:10:41,912 --> 00:10:43,776
I'll go
bring back Ye Chen's head right now.

206
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,320
Dad.

207
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:46,600
Dad,

208
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,159
please calm down.

209
00:10:48,637 --> 00:10:50,741
Ye Chen is already a cripple now.

210
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:52,555
Getting his head won't be difficult.

211
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:08,600
It's too hot today.

212
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,200
Working outside
nearly gave me heatstroke.

213
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,159
I just opened this one.

214
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:12,600
This one is alcohol free.

215
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,440
It works fast too.

216
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:18,125
(Nurse Station)

217
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,600
Excuse me.

218
00:11:21,919 --> 00:11:23,840
Which hospital room
is someone named Ye Chen in?

219
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:24,879
Here to visit?

220
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:25,879
Please register first.

221
00:11:26,070 --> 00:11:27,412
Why are you looking for Ye Chen?

222
00:11:36,137 --> 00:11:38,487
Honey, Mr. Tang,
we need to move right now.

223
00:11:38,639 --> 00:11:39,080
Quick.

224
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,012
We'll talk later.

225
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,225
Check it.

226
00:11:47,679 --> 00:11:48,000
Seven...

227
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,650
Seven zero four.

228
00:11:57,237 --> 00:11:58,000
This is for you.

229
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,399
Thank you, sir.

230
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,559
Quick.

231
00:12:06,912 --> 00:12:07,993
Come on.

232
00:12:34,350 --> 00:12:36,838
♪They said I was only meant
to gaze at the light♪

233
00:12:36,925 --> 00:12:40,678
♪Never knowing I am the flame itself♪

234
00:12:41,138 --> 00:12:46,075
♪I am fireworks, not a fire cast aside♪

235
00:12:46,238 --> 00:12:48,525
♪I open my eyes amid the ruins♪

236
00:12:48,838 --> 00:12:51,518
♪No one shields me
from the wind or the sky♪

237
00:12:52,588 --> 00:12:55,213
♪Let them mock, let them sneer♪

238
00:12:55,513 --> 00:12:58,525
♪I sharpen my silence into blades♪

239
00:12:58,725 --> 00:13:01,775
♪Every cold word, I remember♪

240
00:13:01,888 --> 00:13:04,850
♪Etching my path of defiance
into my heart♪

241
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:08,275
♪Fate did not sign my future for me♪

242
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:12,250
♪I carved my own light
with clenched fists♪

243
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:15,113
♪I belong to no one♪

244
00:13:15,175 --> 00:13:18,625
♪I am the ember
that refuses to bow to destiny♪

245
00:13:18,625 --> 00:13:21,300
♪Even if the world burns me into ash♪

246
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:27,638
♪I will rise upon those ashes♪
